17/09/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Meeting on Friday (15 September), the EU Council praised the way elections were held in Montenegro earlier this month and voiced expectations for a smooth transition of government. The EU foreign ministers also urged authorities in Podgorica to proceed quickly with reforms aimed at strengthening administrative capacities, legislative, judicial and security sectors, in order to quickly launch Stabilisation and Association Agreement talks. (Pobjeda - 16/09/06; EU website - 15/09/06)
